771
00:52:45,702 --> 00:52:48,688
I shouldn't pry into other people's business.

772
00:53:03,640 --> 00:53:05,056
<i>I can't live without you, Hyung.</i>

773
00:53:05,056 --> 00:53:08,074
Oh, that video was in here.

774
00:53:08,074 --> 00:53:10,076
<i>Please don't do this.</i>

775
00:53:10,076 --> 00:53:14,401
<i>You're drunk. I'm going inside first. Please sober up a bit before coming in.</i>

776
00:53:20,271 --> 00:53:21,800
That's refreshing!

777
00:53:21,800 --> 00:53:25,373
I didn't know you were good at drinking!

778
00:53:28,505 --> 00:53:30,977
Well, Ji Won...

779
00:53:31,700 --> 00:53:34,611
Have you ever experienced something like this?

780
00:53:34,611 --> 00:53:36,379
Like what?

781
00:53:37,847 --> 00:53:41,691
Even though you and someone are far apart, you keep thinking about the person.

782
00:53:42,627 --> 00:53:44,987
And if that person is popular with others,

783
00:53:44,987 --> 00:53:47,614
you get annoyed and strangely irritated.

784
00:53:48,691 --> 00:53:54,295
But if you run into that person, you somehow run away.

785
00:53:54,295 --> 00:53:56,490
You have a crush.

786
00:53:57,075 --> 00:53:59,244
Even if you run away?

787
00:53:59,244 --> 00:54:00,745
Think about it.

788
00:54:00,745 --> 00:54:04,189
When you are with that person, does your heart pound?

789
00:54:05,043 --> 00:54:07,528
Well... it seems to be like that.

790
00:54:07,528 --> 00:54:11,172
You feel irritated and annoyed for no reason,

791
00:54:11,172 --> 00:54:14,441
but you become uncomfortable if you don't see that person.

792
00:54:16,344 --> 00:54:18,763
That's a crush!

793
00:54:18,763 --> 00:54:22,874
Why? Do you have someone on your mind lately?

794
00:54:25,583 --> 00:54:29,316
Why are you drinking your beer as if it's water?

795
00:54:29,316 --> 00:54:31,442
You will likely get drunk.

796
00:54:31,442 --> 00:54:33,677
Beer doesn't make me drunk.

797
00:54:36,824 --> 00:54:40,452
Choi Sung Hoon! Hey, you!

798
00:54:41,577 --> 00:54:46,255
Come out... Come out now!

799
00:54:50,378 --> 00:54:51,779
Jay?

800
00:54:51,779 --> 00:54:54,115
Here you are, Sung Hoon.

801
00:54:54,115 --> 00:54:56,802
I missed you!

802
00:54:56,802 --> 00:54:59,494
Wait. Have a seat first.

803
00:55:04,100 --> 00:55:07,643
What happened? Why are you so drunk?

804
00:55:08,813 --> 00:55:12,899
I came here because I missed you. I'm the best, right?

805
00:55:14,527 --> 00:55:18,670
That's good, but... Why did you drink so much?

806
00:55:19,715 --> 00:55:24,371
Do you know how much I struggled all day because of you?

807
00:55:24,371 --> 00:55:26,581
Hey! That's my line.

808
00:55:26,581 --> 00:55:29,959
Where were you? I haven't seen you all afternoon.

809
00:55:30,569 --> 00:55:32,836
I ran away from you.

810
00:55:33,413 --> 00:55:35,456
I tried my best to run away from you.

811
00:55:35,456 --> 00:55:38,825
But wherever I went, you were there.

812
00:55:42,097 --> 00:55:45,575
I said we should take some time apart.

813
00:55:46,577 --> 00:55:49,479
I'm the one who said it's overwhelming,

814
00:55:50,663 --> 00:55:56,025
but I guess I feel the opposite.

815
00:56:01,909 --> 00:56:04,352
Or is my heart

816
00:56:05,327 --> 00:56:07,640
saying that I like you?

817
00:56:09,930 --> 00:56:18,420
♫ <i>Stay in my memory a little longer, just like now</i> ♫

818
00:56:18,420 --> 00:56:25,155
♫ <i>Your figure disappears as you grow distant</i> ♫

819
00:56:25,155 --> 00:56:30,945
<i>This is the moment when friends of 8 years became lovers.</i>

820
00:57:11,891 --> 00:57:13,750
You surprised me!

821
00:57:15,377 --> 00:57:16,879
Your posture is slouched.

822
00:57:16,879 --> 00:57:19,122
I think it's better to push the seat back.

823
00:57:24,448 --> 00:57:25,988
Is it fine?

824
00:57:25,988 --> 00:57:27,072
It's good.

825
00:57:27,072 --> 00:57:31,830
If you feel unwell from drinking heavily last night, rest today.

826
00:57:32,728 --> 00:57:34,746
Right, yesterday...

827
00:57:41,061 --> 00:57:43,046
Are you really okay?

828
00:57:44,592 --> 00:57:47,359
Of course, I'm really fine.

829
00:57:47,359 --> 00:57:48,828
Are you feverish?

830
00:57:48,828 --> 00:57:50,745
I'm telling the truth.

831
00:57:55,451 --> 00:57:58,270
Don't push yourself, and let me know if it's too hard.

832
00:57:58,270 --> 00:57:59,413
Thank you.

833
00:57:59,413 --> 00:58:01,148
Also...

834
00:58:01,148 --> 00:58:03,675
Let's do our assignment together after this.

835
00:58:04,568 --> 00:58:06,320
Okay.

836
00:58:06,320 --> 00:58:07,629
I will work out over there.

837
00:58:07,629 --> 00:58:09,113
All right.

838
00:58:10,933 --> 00:58:13,860
<i>It's good to spend time together.</i>

839
00:58:17,540 --> 00:58:21,040
It's nice out here.
<i>[Wisdom Hall]</i>

840
00:58:23,350 --> 00:58:27,230
♫ <i>(No matter what anyone says) I think of you every day</i> ♫

841
00:58:27,230 --> 00:58:30,770
♫ <i>I miss you every day</i> ♫

842
00:58:30,770 --> 00:58:33,720
♫ <i>I just want to be by your side</i> ♫

843
00:58:33,720 --> 00:58:36,642
After finishing the assignment, the whole day has passed.

844
00:58:36,642 --> 00:58:39,103
But it ended quickly since we did it together.

845
00:58:39,103 --> 00:58:42,947
I wasn't feeling well so you did almost everything for me.

846
00:58:45,251 --> 00:58:50,322
After spending the whole day together, I still feel it is insufficient now that we are going home.

847
00:58:50,322 --> 00:58:52,741
But we will see each other tomorrow at college.

848
00:58:52,741 --> 00:58:55,593
I know, but...

849
00:58:59,072 --> 00:59:01,824
It's getting late. Go inside.

850
00:59:07,624 --> 00:59:10,701
All right. Get home safe.

851
00:59:10,701 --> 00:59:12,636
Don't make me worried.

852
00:59:12,636 --> 00:59:14,220
Okay?

853
00:59:19,460 --> 00:59:21,912
Oh, also...

854
00:59:21,912 --> 00:59:24,697
Do you want to go on a date after class tomorrow?

855
00:59:32,769 --> 00:59:34,630
Right now...

856
00:59:34,630 --> 00:59:38,233
it seems that people feel the same as last year.

857
00:59:38,233 --> 00:59:39,635
"Last year"?

858
00:59:39,635 --> 00:59:43,797
Last year, people stared at me a lot,

859
00:59:43,797 --> 00:59:46,724
since you and I were always together.

860
00:59:46,724 --> 00:59:51,170
And because we are like this now, I'm getting that feeling again.

861
00:59:51,820 --> 00:59:54,115
Now that I think about it, you're right.

862
00:59:56,017 --> 00:59:57,802
But...

863
00:59:58,583 --> 01:00:00,672
It's okay for me.

864
01:00:00,672 --> 01:00:04,593
But if the atmosphere isn't good, we might get swept up in it.

865
01:00:04,593 --> 01:00:08,762
I think it would be better to just stay home and not go out.

866
01:00:08,762 --> 01:00:10,891
Aren't you coming with me?

867
01:00:10,891 --> 01:00:14,227
I have to go somewhere, but I will be right back.

868
01:00:14,227 --> 01:00:15,871
Let me come with you!

869
01:00:15,871 --> 01:00:17,047
No.

870
01:00:17,047 --> 01:00:20,800
I will come by your place immediately after.

871
01:00:22,152 --> 01:00:24,120
Okay, take care of yourself.

872
01:00:25,430 --> 01:00:26,939
See you later.

873
01:00:31,353 --> 01:00:34,130
Does he have to go to that thing today?

874
01:00:49,434 --> 01:00:51,177
What's going on?

875
01:00:51,978 --> 01:00:53,463
I saw it.

876
01:00:53,463 --> 01:00:55,565
I saw Oppa Jin Wook with Jun Sik.

877
01:00:55,565 --> 01:00:57,191
Where?

878
01:00:57,942 --> 01:01:00,077
I saw it on Seung Joo's camera.

879
01:01:02,363 --> 01:01:03,615
That's great information.

880
01:01:03,615 --> 01:01:05,575
My hunch was right.

881
01:01:05,575 --> 01:01:08,211
Let's ask Seung Joo for the footage.

882
01:01:09,186 --> 01:01:14,876
Since he doesn't know that I saw that video, asking for it is a bit of a problem.

883
01:01:14,876 --> 01:01:16,251
Is that so?

884
01:01:16,953 --> 01:01:21,323
Then I will casually ask him at our next group assignment.

885
01:01:22,800 --> 01:01:28,139
But do you really think Oppa Jin Wook is the culprit?

886
01:01:28,139 --> 01:01:29,974
Yes.

887
01:01:29,974 --> 01:01:32,568
There are too many suspicious circumstances.

888
01:01:34,479 --> 01:01:39,301
No wonder. His behavior has been strange lately.

889
01:01:39,301 --> 01:01:42,511
But still, could it really be him?

890
01:01:43,601 --> 01:01:45,555
I'm working hard today as well, picking up litter.

891
01:01:45,555 --> 01:01:47,440
It's quite cool.

892
01:01:47,440 --> 01:01:49,674
Another piece of trash goes in the bin.

893
01:01:51,351 --> 01:01:52,978
Hi, excuse me.

894
01:01:54,780 --> 01:01:56,574
Thank you for the drinks.

895
01:01:56,574 --> 01:01:58,117
I love your YouTube channel.

896
01:01:58,117 --> 01:02:00,436
I don't believe those rumors.

897
01:02:00,436 --> 01:02:04,424
Also, could you give one of these to Oppa Sung Hoon?

898
01:02:05,958 --> 01:02:08,227
Of course. I will hand it to him.

899
01:02:08,227 --> 01:02:10,779
- Thank you!
- Thank you.

900
01:02:24,791 --> 01:02:26,551
- Seung Joo!
- Yes?

901
01:02:26,551 --> 01:02:29,095
I'm just wondering...

902
01:02:29,095 --> 01:02:33,640
Do you have any videos of the day we went to volunteer?

903
01:02:33,640 --> 01:02:38,294
You know, the day that incident happened.

904
01:02:38,294 --> 01:02:39,614
Why do you ask?

905
01:02:39,614 --> 01:02:42,900
I just missed Jun Sik.

906
01:02:43,701 --> 01:02:46,354
No, I have no videos of that day.

907
01:02:57,399 --> 01:02:58,884
What did he say?

908
01:03:00,511 --> 01:03:03,311
Did you perhaps see it wrongly?

909
01:03:03,311 --> 01:03:05,891
I'm sure I didn't.

910
01:03:05,891 --> 01:03:07,518
What the heck?

911
01:03:07,518 --> 01:03:12,213
No, I really saw it! I saw Oppa Jin Wook push Jun Sik down.

912
01:03:34,221 --> 01:03:35,645
Oh?

913
01:03:37,270 --> 01:03:41,980
♫ <i>Because I'm toxic, stay away from me, or else you might get hurt...</i> ♫

914
01:03:41,981 --> 01:03:43,603
Let's install it.

915
01:03:44,421 --> 01:03:46,114
Install what?

916
01:03:46,114 --> 01:03:49,207
A location-tracking app.

917
01:03:49,207 --> 01:03:51,453
Do you have to go to the extent of using a location-tracking app?

918
01:03:51,453 --> 01:03:55,441
It's good to share each other's locations and statuses.

919
01:03:55,441 --> 01:03:57,734
Who knows who might fall into danger?

920
01:03:57,734 --> 01:03:59,460
Sung Hoon...

921
01:03:59,460 --> 01:04:01,100
What do you think?

922
01:04:02,331 --> 01:04:03,823
Yes.

923
01:04:04,441 --> 01:04:06,201
I like the idea.

924
01:04:06,881 --> 01:04:09,306
I could see all of your locations.

925
01:04:11,582 --> 01:04:16,420
But why do you think Seung Joo said there's no video?

926
01:04:16,420 --> 01:04:18,622
She didn't see it incorrectly, right?

927
01:04:18,622 --> 01:04:21,897
I don't think Ji Won would have made that up.

928
01:04:22,547 --> 01:04:24,680
By the way, why is she not coming?

929
01:04:25,285 --> 01:04:27,180
Let me call her.

930
01:04:33,627 --> 01:04:38,637
<i>[Call me when you see this.]
[To Ji Won]</i>

931
01:04:39,457 --> 01:04:41,778
She's not answering so I left a message.

932
01:04:41,778 --> 01:04:45,866
Hey, don't you think we might get a "Brave Citizen Award"

933
01:04:45,866 --> 01:04:48,827
or a "Detective Award" later?

934
01:04:48,827 --> 01:04:53,790
"Students caught the killer based on a citizen's report..."
We could get on the news!

935
01:04:53,790 --> 01:04:56,727
Wow... Daebak.

936
01:04:56,727 --> 01:04:58,987
What a great dream. Do you think it's possible?

937
01:04:58,987 --> 01:05:00,497
Sung Hoon is right.

938
01:05:01,457 --> 01:05:03,807
Oh, that's right! I have an errand to do.

939
01:05:03,807 --> 01:05:05,337
Okay.

940
01:05:06,547 --> 01:05:10,277
Hey, I will install an app and share it with you guys!

941
01:05:10,277 --> 01:05:12,458
- Bye.
- See you.

942
01:05:15,420 --> 01:05:17,860
I'm so stressed lately.

943
01:05:17,860 --> 01:05:22,300
Since we stopped going to the gym due to the situation, my body feels stiff.

944
01:05:23,109 --> 01:05:24,997
Do you want me to massage you?

945
01:05:26,634 --> 01:05:28,085
It feels nice.

946
01:05:28,085 --> 01:05:33,665
Since we are home together, we exercise together, and I get a massage.

947
01:05:33,665 --> 01:05:38,034
We do homework together and eat together.

948
01:05:38,034 --> 01:05:40,172
I feel like this is my home.

949
01:05:40,172 --> 01:05:42,391
Then why don't you live here?

950
01:05:42,391 --> 01:05:45,842
- Can I do that?
- Of course.

951
01:05:45,842 --> 01:05:48,329
No. I was just saying it.

952
01:05:49,214 --> 01:05:53,284
<i>Although these happy little moments are temporary now, in the end,</i>

953
01:05:53,284 --> 01:05:56,104
<i>if this happiness continues, that would be good.</i>

954
01:05:56,104 --> 01:05:58,199
- It hurts. It hurts. Ouch!
- No, it will feel refreshing.

955
01:05:58,199 --> 01:06:00,784
Ouch. Ouch! It hurts there. Don't use your elbows! Don't use them!

956
01:06:00,784 --> 01:06:03,294
No, no, it won't be that painful.

957
01:06:32,644 --> 01:06:34,394
<i>[Ji Won: Call me when you see this.]</i>

958
01:06:42,214 --> 01:06:43,893
Ji Won?

959
01:06:46,784 --> 01:06:49,015
- Thank you so much.
- Thank you.

960
01:06:49,015 --> 01:06:50,900
Thank you.

961
01:07:00,066 --> 01:07:02,276
I'm not the murderer.

962
01:07:02,276 --> 01:07:03,786
What?

963
01:07:05,196 --> 01:07:07,198
I'm saying that I'm not the murderer.

964
01:07:07,198 --> 01:07:11,269
I don't know why you guys suspect me.

965
01:07:11,269 --> 01:07:14,856
- But you've got it wrong.
- That bloody hand plow in the gym's storage room.

966
01:07:14,856 --> 01:07:17,115
How do you explain that?

967
01:07:18,151 --> 01:07:20,111
Prove it.

968
01:07:20,111 --> 01:07:22,629
That you weren't at the site of the incident.

969
01:07:25,033 --> 01:07:27,742
Sure. Fine.

970
01:07:34,792 --> 01:07:36,853
It was this day.

971
01:07:36,853 --> 01:07:41,274
After the volunteer work, I came straight to the gym to exercise.

972
01:07:41,274 --> 01:07:46,059
After an hour or so, I got a message from Jun Sik.

973
01:07:47,572 --> 01:07:52,368
He had something to tell me one last time and wanted to meet right away.

974
01:07:52,368 --> 01:07:54,211
<i>Jun Sik.</i>

975
01:08:02,987 --> 01:08:04,780
<i>J-Jun Sik...</i>

976
01:08:07,141 --> 01:08:08,976
<i>Hey, Jun Sik!</i>

977
01:08:10,495 --> 01:08:14,490
<i>Hey, Jun Sik... Jun Sik!</i>

978
01:08:14,490 --> 01:08:19,230
<i>Come to your senses, Jun Sik!</i>

979
01:08:19,230 --> 01:08:20,722
<i>No... Jun Sik...</i>

980
01:08:20,722 --> 01:08:23,983
<i>Please wake up, Jun Sik!</i>

981
01:08:23,983 --> 01:08:27,895
<i>Is there anyone there? Help!</i>

982
01:08:27,895 --> 01:08:29,872
<i>Jun Sik, please...</i>

983
01:09:19,581 --> 01:09:22,850
<i>One day, someone put the bloody hand plow in the storage room.</i>

984
01:09:22,850 --> 01:09:25,670
<i>I had definitely washed it and thrown it away.</i>

985
01:09:25,670 --> 01:09:29,039
<i>I got scared so I wrapped it in newspapers and hid it.</i>

986
01:09:32,606 --> 01:09:35,734
The culprit... is threatening me.

987
01:09:35,734 --> 01:09:38,821
He wants the rumor to spread and frame me as the murderer.

988
01:09:38,821 --> 01:09:40,581
Then the real murderer is–

989
01:09:40,581 --> 01:09:44,284
Someone around us who knows us well.

990
01:09:44,284 --> 01:09:47,412
And that might be Seung Joo.

991
01:09:53,335 --> 01:09:56,130
The midterms are just around the corner.

992
01:09:56,130 --> 01:09:57,423
It's nice weather today.

993
01:09:57,423 --> 01:09:59,065
Seung Joo.

994
01:10:04,558 --> 01:10:08,995
We are going to check Hyung Jin Wook's alibi today.

995
01:10:08,995 --> 01:10:10,729
You should come with us.

996
01:10:11,998 --> 01:10:14,250
All right then.

997
01:10:14,250 --> 01:10:16,051
See you guys later.

998
01:10:18,229 --> 01:10:20,989
There's a new event this evening.

999
01:10:28,379 --> 01:10:30,348
Did you tell Hyung Jin Wook about the plan?

1000
01:10:30,348 --> 01:10:34,176
I did everything as planned, but will he really take the bait?

1001
01:10:34,176 --> 01:10:35,970
Act normally when Seung Joo comes.

1002
01:10:35,970 --> 01:10:40,366
If he's really the murderer, as Hyung suspects, he will take the bait.

1003
01:10:40,366 --> 01:10:43,669
Isn't this too dangerous? And what if Seung Joo also isn't the culprit?

1004
01:10:43,669 --> 01:10:46,881
Don't worry. No matter who the culprit is, I'll protect you.

1005
01:10:46,881 --> 01:10:50,715
Guys... he's coming.

1006
01:10:51,485 --> 01:10:54,112
We need to execute this perfectly.

1007
01:10:55,422 --> 01:10:58,107
- You're here!
- Yes.

1008
01:11:01,604 --> 01:11:03,464
Sorry, I'm late.

1009
01:11:14,930 --> 01:11:17,320
We are looking pretty neutral right now.

1010
01:11:25,260 --> 01:11:26,290
Are you okay?

1011
01:11:26,290 --> 01:11:30,730
I didn't drink water when I ate the chicken breast earlier. My throat is sore.

1012
01:11:38,720 --> 01:11:43,920
If Hyung Jin Wook comes out before you return, we will follow him, so keep in touch.

1013
01:11:51,958 --> 01:11:56,391
Guys, sorry. I need the bathroom.

1014
01:12:26,258 --> 01:12:28,975
<i>Wouldn't this be too sweet?</i>

1015
01:12:28,975 --> 01:12:31,353
<i>But would this be too bland?</i>

1016
01:12:33,771 --> 01:12:38,308
<i>Well, I'll give you everything you want.</i>

1017
01:12:46,327 --> 01:12:47,921
Sung Hoon!

1018
01:12:55,600 --> 01:12:58,052
He must have followed you.

1019
01:12:58,750 --> 01:13:01,608
Ki Hyeon will catch up to us, won't he?

1020
01:13:01,608 --> 01:13:02,817
It will be all right.

1021
01:13:02,817 --> 01:13:06,550
He would have followed him, so we would know when Ki Hyeon shows up.

1022
01:13:08,936 --> 01:13:11,267
I hope what you said is true.

1023
01:13:11,267 --> 01:13:13,789
If not, it won't be good for you either.

